Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Coal and Steel Community, and in particular Article 95 thereof,
Whereas, following the Council Decision of 25 February 1991, the Commission conducted negotiations with the Czech and Slovak Federal Republic which have resulted in a Protocol on trade and commercial and economic cooperation in respect of products  covered by the ECSC Treaty;
Whereas the conclusion of this Agreement is indispensable for the attainment of the objectives of the Community as defined inter alia in Articles 2 and 3 of the Treaty establishing the ECSC;
Whereas this Decision does not affect the powers of the Member States in matters of commercial policy referred to in Article 71 of the Treaty;
